subSubSection.paragraph:
Hypopygium
(
Figs 31–32
). Anal point 11–43, 24 µm long, tapering to pointed apex; tergite IX with 10– 24, 15 setae including setae on anal point. Laterosternite IX with 2–5, 4 setae. Phallapodeme 59–79, 70 (7) µm long. Transverse sternapodeme 45–75, 57 µm long, with weak oral projections. Virga 9–18, 13 µm long; plate-like. Pars ventralis (
Fig. 33
) double, 75–120, 93 µm long; 34–71, 42 µm wide; reaching to 0.50–0.76 gonocoxite length. Gonocoxite 140–179, 160 µm long. Inferior volsella reaching to 0.65–0.69 gonocoxite length; no apparent posterior lobe. Gonostylus 61–79, 68 µm long; megaseta 6–9, 8 µm long. HR 2.07–2.51, 2.36. HV 2.91–3.88, 3.22.
